This paper proposes a new object detection model that uses a mixture model for density estimation. The paper focuses on computer vision tasks, specifically object detection, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category. The use of a mixture model also suggests that it may belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new network structure and objective function, which further supports the possibility of it belonging to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. The use of categorical distributions may also suggest a connection to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on benchmark datasets, which may suggest a connection to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) category.
